               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-297-person2726">
                  JOHN 
                  DEAN
               <interp inst="t18200918-297-person2726" type="surname" value="DEAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-297-person2726" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-297-person2726" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Swallow-street. On the 30th of August, about five o'clock in the afternoon, I was in <placeName id="t18200918-297-crimeloc1704">St. James's square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-297-crimeloc1704" type="placeName" value="St. James's square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-297-crimeloc1704" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-297-off1702 t18200918-297-crimeloc1704"></join> when the Clerkenwell address was being presented to the Queen. The Queen's carriage came up; there was a very heavy pressure from the crowd; two females were before me, who cried for assistance; while my hands were up endeavouring to protect them, I felt something at my pocket, put my hands down and missed my pocket-book, which was safe a moment before; the prisoner was close to me; I instantly seized him, and said,</p>
               <p>"You scoundrel, you have taken my pocket-book!" two men immediately seized him and asked me to let him go, but I held him. I found they were officers and I gave him up to them; one of them immediately pulled my pocket-book from his breeches.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-297-person2727">
                  JOHN 
                  FURZEMAN
               <interp inst="t18200918-297-person2727" type="surname" value="FURZEMAN"></interp>
